| `Hubbard/HopSignBetween.lean` | **Forward-hop JW sign as a strictly-between parity** (Issue #4230 PR3c-3): `jwSign_mul_jwSign_update_forward` — for a forward hop `q→p` (`q.val<p.val`, source `c q=1`), `jwSign q c · jwSign p (update c q 0) = (-1)^(#occupied modes strictly between q,p)`; the `2·E_q` of the modes below the source cancels in parity. `jwSign_mul_jwSign_update_backward` — the backward analogue (`p.val<q.val`, target `c p=0`) `= (-1)^(#strictly between p,q)`. Model-agnostic; underlies the sign-free d=1 t-J hopping. Axiom-free |
